reviews.review: was not entertaining. only went cause my daughter wanted to go. i was surprised in how bad it was.
"The Emoji Movie" isn't necessarily the end of cinema, or among the worst films ever made, but regardless, the film still suffers from unfunny comedy and a predictable plot-line.
THIS MOVIE WAS INCREDIBLE! NO COMPLAINTS. THIS IS THE ONLY MOVIE I WOULD SEE ON MY DEATHBED.

This is possibly the greatest and most amazing piece of cinema I have ever seen! I saw it last night and it was so beautiful it brought me to tears. Such an amazingly written, amazingly directed, amazingly animated movie! Easily the greatest movie so far This year, I would recommend bringing the whole family to this, there is amazing humour and jokes in it, by the five minute mark I was rolling on the ground slapping me knee cause it was so funny! Especially the poop emoji with all of the hilarious and original toilet humor! Don't listen to the negative reviews cause those people are all just haters and don't understand the true brilliance of this movie! I will be spending my $956 dollar pay check on seeing the emoji movie every day this month. I will be bringing everyone I know to this masterpiece! I downloaded the amazing and original soundtrack when I got home and today I spendt $400 on emoji movie merchandise! Please go see this movie cause it is truly amazing! P.S. I definitely wasn't the person who was pleasuring myself in the theatre. The only part I didn't absolutely love is the fact that there was no ??? Emoji! Have a good day thanks for reading my review!????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????????

This movie absolutely stinks. Even my 8 and 10 year olds hated it. No story line, not funny, and no message either. The highlight was the popcorn. Trying to think of other ways to slam this move but I'm speechless. How do people put this stuff out? A new low for Hollywood.
